gomodel:SYNGO_1191  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Expression of Glycine receptor subunits to show functional (ion-channel) properties, here measured by single channel measurements in out-side-out patch configuration.\n\nrule: NAS_MFCC-BP\nrationale:\nProtein has ligand-gated ion channel receptor activity and is localized in the presynaptic membrane (shown with high-resolution technique). The inference to term ligand-gated ion channel activity involved in regulation of presynaptic membrane potential (GO:0099507) is trivial and non-controversial.\nPinf_CC:\n[P07727] SyNGO ID 1129 (PMID:23175852, EM). Experimental description: For transfection, the human al and cx2 (Grenningloh, 1990a), ratc3 (Kuhse etal.,1990)andratfl(Grenninglohetal.,1990b)subunitcDNAs were insertedintothemammalianexpressionvectorspCIS2(Gormanetal.,1989) orpRC/CMV (Invitrogen),bothofwhichcarryacytomegaloviruspromoter.\n\np.3730: Expression of homoand hetero-oligomeric GlyRsTransfectionofHEK-293cellswitha 1, U2orO3subunitcDNAs resulted in the formation of functional homo-oligomericchannels,whichwere studiedbywhole-cellrecording. -- Highlighted 07 Aug 2017" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9425-2935" ;
        dc:date           "2018-06-29" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_MF_1191" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_9606" .

